sentences: Born in 1908, she lost her parents early and was brought up by her aunt, the noted singer Rajeshwari Devi.
In 1989, noted director Mani Kaul made an award-winning documentary, Siddheshwari, on her lifeShe won many accolades during her career, including:
Padma Shri by the Government of India (1966)
Honorary D. Lit. degree by the Ravindra Bharati Vishwavidyalaya in Kolkata (1973)
She died on 18 March 1977 in New Delhi.
Siddheswari Devi (1908– 18 March 1977) was a legendary Hindustani singer from Varanasi, India, known as Maa (mother).
The next day, Siyaji Maharaj came to Rajeshwari, and asked to adopt Siddheswari into his own family (they were childless).
On several occasions she would sing perform through the night, for example on the overnight boating expeditions of Maharaja of Darbhanga.
